What is Flask?

Flask is a lightweight, micro web framework in Python used to build web applications and REST APIs.

 Features of Flask:--

Lightweight & fast
Easy and flexible
Built-in development server
Uses Jinja2 template engine
Supports routing & REST API development
Good for small to medium projects

 Installation:--
pip install flask

 Basic Flask Program:--
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "Hello Flask"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
